

     
      Designing.... not developing J2ME application. This is an excellent article from IBM and I recommend a must read before taking up J2ME based projects.  When designing software applications for devices such as cell phones and PDAs, you must consider any potential problems, such as resource-challenged platforms for instance. With those tasks in mind, author Mikko Kontio walks you through the design process for MIDP-based applications.  [Resource-Type: Article; Category: Java/J2ME; Level: IMD/ADV, XRating: 5]
     
    
